Upcoming

1.8.0
- major search performance improvement: matches to report are precomputed per state and
  for string inputs stretches of text in which no keyword can start are skipped using a
  precompiled regex character class. Searching text with few matches is now ~6x faster
  and on par with the pyahocorasick C extension (faster than it on pypy), match-dense
  text is ~25-40% faster. Setup takes slightly longer due to the precomputation.
- performance test now also measures a match-dense scenario and collects garbage between
  timings to keep gc pauses (mainly on pypy) out of the search measurements
- refreshed performance comparison numbers in README (CPython 3.14, PyPy 7.3.23, latest library versions)

1.7.0
- updated python compatibility matrix
- got rid of "future" dependency (#16)
- documented and added test coverage for matching arbitrary sequences of hashable symbols (#14)
- repo got transfered from abusix to FrederikP

